<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>
<!-- Generated by Pandoc using pretext.lua -->
<worksheet>
  <title>Homework 4</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
      <alert>Foundations of Mathematics</alert>
    </p>
  </introduction>

	<p><ol>
		<li>
			<p>
				Suppose <m>a\in{\bf Z}</m>. Prove that if <m>a^2 | a</m>, then <m>a\in \{-1,0,1\}</m>.
			</p>
		</li>

		<li>
			<p>
				Suppose that <m>a,b\in{\bf Z}</m>. Prove that <m>10a - 15b\neq 3</m>.
			</p>
		</li>

		<li>
			<p>
				Prove that for any <m>a,b\in{\bf Z}</m>, <m>(a + b)^3\equiv a^3 + b^3\ (\mbox{mod }3)</m>.
			</p>
		</li>

		<li>
			<p>
				Suppose <m>x</m> and <m>y</m> are real numbers.
			</p>
		
			<p><ol>
				<li>
					<p>
						Prove that if <m>(x+y)^3 = x^3 + y^3</m>, then <m>x=0</m>, <m>y=0</m>, or <m>y = -x</m>.
					</p>
				</li>
		
				<li>
					<p>
						Prove the converse, that if <m>x=0</m>, <m>y=0</m>, or <m>y = -x</m>, then <m>(x+y)^3 = x^3 + y^3</m>.
					</p>
				</li>
		
			</ol></p>
		
			<p>
				<em>Remark.</em> Together, the two parts of this question prove that <m>(x+y)^3 = x^3 + y^3</m> if and only if <m>x=0</m>, <m>y=0</m>, or <m>y = -x</m>.
			</p>
		
			<p>
				<em>Hint.</em> There is a similar odd exercise in Chapter 7.
			</p>
		</li>

	</ol></p>

